text: The Newell Highway is a major road in New South Wales, Australia. It runs from the Queensland border to the Victoria border. It is New South Wales's longest highway. It is almost long. It is the main road between Brisbane and Melbourne. The Newell Highway runs through some large towns such as Moree, Dubbo, Parkes and Narrandera.
